song_name: Can You Please Crawl Out Your Window

version_description: Alternate version ("rehearsal with pedal steel" - Sept 23, 1980) with different chords and lyrics.

I initially wanted to suggest a correction to another submission of this piece, but found my own version sufficiently different to warrant a separate submission. I would point out that the original release of this song contained minor variations in the chord progression, as many Dylan works do. This is a work from ear, not a songbook, but these chords work very well.
Fixed the lyrics in several places. Added intro and outro. Extended the chords out through the entire song.
Complete and well-aligned chords for the whole song.

song_name: Coming From The Heart The Road Is Long

performance.name: Live at Civic Center, St. Paul, MN, 10/31/1978

version_description: This is not the same key and these are not the identical chords used by Mr. Dylan on his recording but they work and the key can be changed to suit your voice. This is an old folk song and I've added the chords the way I remember first hearing it. It may well have been Joan Baez where I heard it or even somewhere else. I do apologize for any misunderstanding caused by me in using Bob Dylan as the artist and I have been unable to change that in the heading.
Complete chords for Dylan's version of the song released on "Self Portrait" and "The Bootleg Series Vol. 10" / ear-transcribed and readably formatted.
Complete chords and lyrics / well-aligned / suggestions for voicings of special chords / capo 3rd fret to match Dylan's studio recording.
